history.content: I think 61c you can safely phase 2. 16b I would phase 1 though.

16B requires 16A as an absolute hard prereq. There are 490 seats in 16B. There are about 480 people in 16A this term. There are about 10ish other students out there who took the 16A pilot and did not take the 16B pilot.

What deduction can you make for this regarding the supply vs demand in 16B? 

What consequences might this have upon your decision to phase 1 vs phase 2 the course?

We expect all the EECS students taking 16A this term to take 16B next term. There will be enough seats for them in 16B. 

61C will have spots held through the final date of undergrad phase II telebears appointments (December 10) for declared EECS majors (see http://www.eecs.berkeley.edu/Policies/enrollment.shtml ).
